STATE OF CONNECTICUT v. JOHN NARANJO (13353)

Dupont, C. J., and Foti and Spallone, Js.

Argued November 1 decision released November 28, 1995 John R. Williams, for the appellant (defendant). Ronald G. Weller, deputy assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Michael Dearington, state’s attorney, and James Rinnan, assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
